# Quality Checks

- Prefer focused changes that preserve existing module boundaries and user work.
- Run `npm run agents:check` after changing Codex skills, Cursor rules, or agent-facing docs.
- Run `npm run lint:ci` from `localpaas-dashboard/` for frontend code changes when feasible.
- Run `npm run build` when route exports, module aggregators, API context wiring, or build configuration changed.
- Run `npm run format:src` only when formatting source files intentionally; avoid broad formatting churn.
- For visible UI changes, run `npm run dev` and verify the affected screen in a browser when feasible.
- Report any skipped validation with the exact blocker.

# Dependency And Generated Files

- Do not add dependencies unless the existing stack cannot reasonably solve the task.
- Do not touch `package-lock.json` or `yarn.lock` unless dependencies are intentionally changed.
- Do not manually edit generated OpenAPI output under `src/infrastructure/api/be-api/**`.
- Do not run codegen, format-all, or dependency install commands as part of agent setup changes unless explicitly requested.
